5081#define HEADERBUF  (128*1024)
5082int
5083RTMP_Read(RTMP *r, char *buf, int size)
5084{
5085    int nRead = 0, total = 0;
5086
5087    /* can't continue */
5088fail:
5089    switch (r->m_read.status)
5090    {
5091    case RTMP_READ_EOF:
5092    case RTMP_READ_COMPLETE:
5093        return 0;
5094    case RTMP_READ_ERROR:  /* corrupted stream, resume failed */
5095        SetSockError(EINVAL);
5096        return -1;
5097    default:
5098        break;
5099    }
5100
5101    /* first time thru */
5102    if (!(r->m_read.flags & RTMP_READ_HEADER))
5103    {
5104        if (!(r->m_read.flags & RTMP_READ_RESUME))
5105        {
5106            char *mybuf = malloc(HEADERBUF), *end = mybuf + HEADERBUF;
5107            int cnt = 0;
5108            r->m_read.buf = mybuf;
5109            r->m_read.buflen = HEADERBUF;
5110
5111            memcpy(mybuf, flvHeader, sizeof(flvHeader));
5112            r->m_read.buf += sizeof(flvHeader);
5113            r->m_read.buflen -= sizeof(flvHeader);
5114            cnt += sizeof(flvHeader);
5115
5116            while (r->m_read.timestamp == 0)
5117            {
5118                nRead = Read_1_Packet(r, r->m_read.buf, r->m_read.buflen);
5119                if (nRead < 0)
5120                {
5121                    free(mybuf);
5122                    r->m_read.buf = NULL;
5123                    r->m_read.buflen = 0;
5124                    r->m_read.status = nRead;
5125                    goto fail;
5126                }
5127                /* buffer overflow, fix buffer and give up */
5128                if (r->m_read.buf < mybuf || r->m_read.buf > end)
5129                {
5130                    mybuf = realloc(mybuf, cnt + nRead);
5131                    memcpy(mybuf+cnt, r->m_read.buf, nRead);
5132                    free(r->m_read.buf);
5133                    r->m_read.buf = mybuf+cnt+nRead;
5134                    break;
5135                }
5136                cnt += nRead;
5137                r->m_read.buf += nRead;
5138                r->m_read.buflen -= nRead;
5139                if (r->m_read.dataType == 5)
5140                    break;
5141            }
5142            mybuf[4] = r->m_read.dataType;
5143            r->m_read.buflen = r->m_read.buf - mybuf;
5144            r->m_read.buf = mybuf;
5145            r->m_read.bufpos = mybuf;
5146        }
5147        r->m_read.flags |= RTMP_READ_HEADER;
5148    }
5149
5150    if ((r->m_read.flags & RTMP_READ_SEEKING) && r->m_read.buf)
5151    {
5152        /* drop whatever's here */
5153        free(r->m_read.buf);
5154        r->m_read.buf = NULL;
5155        r->m_read.bufpos = NULL;
5156        r->m_read.buflen = 0;
5157    }
5158
5159    /* If there's leftover data buffered, use it up */
5160    if (r->m_read.buf)
5161    {
5162        nRead = r->m_read.buflen;
5163        if (nRead > size)
5164            nRead = size;
5165        memcpy(buf, r->m_read.bufpos, nRead);
5166        r->m_read.buflen -= nRead;
5167        if (!r->m_read.buflen)
5168        {
5169            free(r->m_read.buf);
5170            r->m_read.buf = NULL;
5171            r->m_read.bufpos = NULL;
5172        }
5173        else
5174        {
5175            r->m_read.bufpos += nRead;
5176        }
5177        buf += nRead;
5178        total += nRead;
5179        size -= nRead;
5180    }
5181
5182    while (size > 0 && (nRead = Read_1_Packet(r, buf, size)) >= 0)
5183    {
5184        if (!nRead) continue;
5185        buf += nRead;
5186        total += nRead;
5187        size -= nRead;
5188        break;
5189    }
5190    if (nRead < 0)
5191        r->m_read.status = nRead;
5192
5193    if (size < 0)
5194        total += size;
5195    return total;
5196}

5200int
5201RTMP_Write(RTMP *r, const char *buf, int size, int streamIdx)
5202{
5203    RTMPPacket *pkt = &r->m_write;
5204    char *pend, *enc;
5205    int s2 = size, ret, num;
5206
5207    pkt->m_nChannel = 0x04;  /* source channel */
5208    pkt->m_nInfoField2 = r->Link.streams[streamIdx].id;
5209
5210    while (s2)
5211    {
5212        if (!pkt->m_nBytesRead)
5213        {
5214            if (size < 11)
5215            {
5216                /* FLV pkt too small */
5217                return 0;
5218            }
5219
5220            if (buf[0] == 'F' && buf[1] == 'L' && buf[2] == 'V')
5221            {
5222                buf += 13;
5223                s2 -= 13;
5224            }
5225
5226            pkt->m_packetType = *buf++;
5227            pkt->m_nBodySize = AMF_DecodeInt24(buf);
5228            buf += 3;
5229            pkt->m_nTimeStamp = AMF_DecodeInt24(buf);
5230            buf += 3;
5231            pkt->m_nTimeStamp |= *buf++ << 24;
5232            buf += 3;
5233            s2 -= 11;
5234
5235            if (((pkt->m_packetType == RTMP_PACKET_TYPE_AUDIO
5236                    || pkt->m_packetType == RTMP_PACKET_TYPE_VIDEO) &&
5237                    !pkt->m_nTimeStamp) || pkt->m_packetType == RTMP_PACKET_TYPE_INFO)
5238            {
5239                pkt->m_headerType = RTMP_PACKET_SIZE_LARGE;
5240                if (pkt->m_packetType == RTMP_PACKET_TYPE_INFO)
5241                    pkt->m_nBodySize += 16;
5242            }
5243            else
5244            {
5245                pkt->m_headerType = RTMP_PACKET_SIZE_MEDIUM;
5246            }
5247
5248            if (!RTMPPacket_Alloc(pkt, pkt->m_nBodySize))
5249            {
5250                RTMP_Log(RTMP_LOGDEBUG, "%s, failed to allocate packet", __FUNCTION__);
5251                return FALSE;
5252            }
5253            enc = pkt->m_body;
5254            pend = enc + pkt->m_nBodySize;
5255            if (pkt->m_packetType == RTMP_PACKET_TYPE_INFO)
5256            {
5257                enc = AMF_EncodeString(enc, pend, &av_setDataFrame);
5258                pkt->m_nBytesRead = enc - pkt->m_body;
5259            }
5260        }
5261        else
5262        {
5263            enc = pkt->m_body + pkt->m_nBytesRead;
5264        }
5265        num = pkt->m_nBodySize - pkt->m_nBytesRead;
5266        if (num > s2)
5267            num = s2;
5268        memcpy(enc, buf, num);
5269        pkt->m_nBytesRead += num;
5270        s2 -= num;
5271        buf += num;
5272        if (pkt->m_nBytesRead == pkt->m_nBodySize)
5273        {
5274            ret = RTMP_SendPacket(r, pkt, FALSE);
5275            RTMPPacket_Free(pkt);
5276            pkt->m_nBytesRead = 0;
5277            if (!ret)
5278                return -1;
5279            buf += 4;
5280            s2 -= 4;
5281            if (s2 < 0)
5282                break;
5283        }
5284    }
5285    return size+s2;
5286}
